# Jamf Pro API rules

## Source of truth: developer.jamf.com

When in doubt about an endpoint's shape — request body, response envelope, query params, error codes — **consult the public developer portal first**. Don't infer from Patcher's existing code; the upstream contract updates with each Jamf Pro release and is the canonical reference.

**Primary references** (public, no authentication required):

- https://developer.jamf.com/jamf-pro/reference — rendered Swagger UI for the Jamf Pro API (every endpoint, request/response shapes, parameter docs)
- https://developer.jamf.com/developer-guide — the top-level developer guide hub
- https://developer.jamf.com/developer-guide/docs/api-style-guide — Jamf's own conventions for API design (useful for predicting how new endpoints will be shaped)
- https://developer.jamf.com/developer-guide/docs/jamf-pro-api-scalability-best-practices — concurrency, rate limits, throttling guidance

